The paper is about artificial neural networks and their flexibility in terms of structure evolution during training. This topic is most closely related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which focuses on the design, analysis, and application of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. The paper also discusses the use of gradient descent and loss functions, which are common techniques in machine learning and fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the geometric properties of input data, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and possibly systems and control (cs.SY) as well.
